Whitney Bourne https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Whitney_Bourne 0 Whitney Bourne (May 6, 1914 – December 24, 1988) was an American stage and film actress. She was a leading lady in several B films of the 1930s, with occasional appearances in more prestigious films such as the British musical Head over Heels. During WWII, she was an "American Red Cross" clubmobiler. Whitney_Bourne ( May_6_,_1914 – December_24 , 1988 ) was an_American_stage_and_film_actress .
